prj:TechnicalJustification.prj:justificationText:
Science Goal 1 covers red SPIRE sources with #01 - 11
(1)Requested sensitivity
At z=3.1, the S(350) = 25 mJy limit corresponds to a FIR luminosity of L(FIR) ~1.2 * 10^13 L(sun) with a dust temperature of 40K. We assume a SMG-SMG mergers with FIR luminosity ratio of 1:3, a [CII] and FIR luminosity ratio of L[CII] / L[FIR] ~ 0.1%, and a line width of 500 km/s. The faintest source should have a [CII] line luminosity of L[CII] ~3 * 10^(9) L(sun) or a peak flux density of 36 mJy per 500 km/s.
If we assume to use band 3 CO(4-3) for same 10 SNR, 2.4 hours is required for each sources on-source time, and 4.4 hours including overhead, therefore [CII] observation is expected to have about 34 times efficient. [CII] observation with ALMA is only and powerful tool for FIR luminous large samples.
(2)Imaging requiement
The required resolution corresponds to the typical SMG sizes ~5 kpc, which enable us to resolve SMG-SMG mergers. We need 5 pointings to cover a single 18" SPIRE beam at 250 um and 2 tunings to cover the protocluster redshift range of z=3.05-3.12. Therefore we request 4.5 hours including overhead.
(3)Correlator setup
We will use the spectral-scan mode with FDM 1875-MHz. Two frequency tunings cover 461.0-468.5 GHz.
(4)User-defined calibration
None
(5)Bandpass accuracy
The expected FWZI of line is up to 1000 km/s. We don't need especially higher accuuracies.
(6)Scheduling/time constraint:
None.
(7)Data rate 0.7 MB/s, which is below the data limit.
(8)Special constraints
None.

prp:ObsProposal.prp:abstract:
We propose band8 [CII] 158um observations of 34 Herschel SPIRE sources in SSA22 protocluster field. We selected the red SPIRE sources, which could be z>2. The projected surface number density of the SPIRE sources is 1.7 times higher than the average in other 12 blank fields, suggesting that the 14 SPIRE sources could reside in the protocluster at z = 3.1. We have two major goals.
[1] The space density of SMGs in the protocluster: We could quantify the real space density of the SPIRE sources in the protocluster by determination of redshift. If predicted 14 SPIRE sources are really protocluster members, the space density would be about 100 times larger than the field environment.
[2] The frequency of SMG-SMG mergers in the protocluster: Several known SMG-SMG merger systems at z>2 have studied,but relationship between SMG-SMG mergers and protoclusters is unclear. The ALMA observations will enable us to test the frequent mergers predicted by Cosmological numerical simulations.
prp:ObsProposal.prp:scientificCategoryString: Cosmology and the High Redshift Universe
